KZN government tables budget votes PIETERMARITZBURG -Â The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Government Departments are tabling departmental budgets in the KwaZulu-Natal Legislature which are expected to respond to the recent flood-related disaster. The budget votes will give a clear indication of the magnitude and resources required to rebuild the province following the recent devastating floods, the effects of COVID-19 and the July unrest. The focus will be on the Department of Agriculture and Rural Development, Social Development, Education and Human Settlements.  KZN government tables budget votes [No. 08/2022 FOURTH SESSION, SIXTH LEGISLATURE 06 May 2022 1. Vote 14 Public Works 2. Vote 3 Agriculture and Rural Development